# JavaScript Development Guidelines

## JS Plugin Development
- JS plugins use `componentize-js` and must implement the shared WIT interface
- Reference [api-js/index.js](mdc:api-js/index.js) for implementation patterns
- Ensure JS plugins match the shared WIT interface structure in [wit/shared-api.wit](mdc:wit/shared-api.wit)

## Build Commands
```bash
# Build JS component
cd api-js && npm run build
```

## Development Setup
```bash
# Enter Nix devShell with all tools
nix develop

# This provides: Rust, Spin, Wasm tools, Node.js, etc.
# Auto-starts zsh and installs JS dependencies for api-js
```

## Package Management
- Dependencies are managed in [api-js/package.json](mdc:api-js/package.json)
- Use `componentize.js` for building Wasm components from JavaScript
- Node.js is provided via Nix devShell for consistency
